                <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uinto</ex></expan> Marcio Barea <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan> Rustio Nu<supplied reason="lost">mmio</supplied> <lb n="3"/>Gallo <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="4"/>senatus populusque Baxonensis <lb n="5"/>hospitium fecit cum colonis co<lb break="no" n="6"/>loniae Claritatis Iuliae ipsis <lb n="7"/>liberis posterisque suis <lb n="8"/>egerunt <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ati</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> Fabius <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uinti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Rufus <lb n="10"/><expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Terentius <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ubli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Macer </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Armeni felix <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratore</ex></expan> <del rend="erasure">[Philippo</del>] <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>et <del rend="erasure">Ph[ilippo</del>] <expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>are</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>collegium corporis fabro<lb break="no" n="5"/>rum sub<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>edianorum</abbr></expan> Patri<lb break="no" n="6"/>c<expan><ex>i</ex><abbr>ensium</abbr></expan> Cordubensium <lb n="7"/>Bellum Licinianum se libe<lb break="no" n="8"/><expan><abbr>rosq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> suos patronum coopta<lb break="no" n="9"/>verunt postea Bellus Licinia<lb break="no" n="10"/>nus corpus <expan><abbr>fabror</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> sub<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>edianor</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <lb n="11"/>Cordubensium Patric<expan><ex>i</ex><abbr>ens</abbr><ex>ium</ex></expan> in <lb n="12"/>familiam clientelamque suam <lb n="13"/>recepit
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): Leseabweichungen. Rückseite der Bronzetafel ist sekundär mit einer tabula patronatus beschriftet worden; Datierung: 247 n. Chr.</p>
